race.comment: PROPRIETARY (2) hasn't won for a long time but has found some form, placing in his last four. Was good again last time when beaten less than a length at Burrumbeet over a similar trip. He has enough pace to offset the wide alley and gets his chance to break a long run of outs. LAYBUY (3) didn't give his rivals a sniff fresh when leading all the way. Was good second-up at Tatura but struggled last time in tough conditions. Freshened with 7 weeks and drops back to a winning trip. Expect him to bounce back sharply. COLD TRAIN (9) has found the maiden win elusive but has efforts littered through his form that has him in the mix. HE'S ELECTRIC (12) is another still looking to get off the mark but finds a thin race and the low weight gives him a chance.
